#TIL tidyr::unnest() has a parameter names_repair to automate fixing names when unnesting data frames to ensure valid column names and unique, among other options #RStats https://t.co/Aq4OPbkgMl

with <10 lines of #RStats code, you too can explore trends in nobel prizes

library(tidyverse)
u <- "https://t.co/X2xU0AOx7A"
a <- jsonlite::fromJSON(u, flatten = TRUE)
nobel_tbl <- tibble(a$laureates)
nobel <- nobel_tbl %>%
  unnest(nobelPrizes) %>%
  janitor::clean_names()

*#RStats correction

nobel <- nobel_tbl %>%
    tidyr::unnest(nobelPrizes, names_repair = "unique") %>%
    janitor::clean_names()
